        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Higher Education",
          "Not Applicable",
          "Predicting Student Dropout During the First Year",
          "Dropout (+) vs No Dropout (-)",
          "3750 first-year engineering students from UAI\n\n2201 first-year engineering students from Universidad de Talca\n\n\n\n\n\n",
          "Limited to Engineering Students",
          "Student Demographics, \nHighschool History and Characteristics, Application data, University Admission Test Scores",
          "[Year, Gender, School, Admission, Nem, Ranking, Mat, Lang, Optional, Pps, Preference, Commune, Region, University]",
          "Start of First Year",
          "From description, data follows a standard ML pipeline: \n\nBinning and aggregations, Feature Selection etc..\n\nClass Imabalances are addressed by Undersampling of the Majority Class.\n\nNominal Variables were One-Hot Encoded for Tree-based Models.\n\nBoth datasets are reduced to a small portion of their initial sizes due to the Data Cleaning Efforts.",
          "kNN\nSVM\nNaive Bayes\nDT\nRandom Forest\nGBoost\nMLP\nLogistic Regression",
          "10-Fold Cross-Validation",
          "{F1-Score: 0,37 - GBoost, Recall: 0.58 - kNN, Precision: 0.28 - RF & GBoost, Accuracy: GBoost & RF}",
          "Optimal Combination of Hyper-Parameters for each algorithm were assessed via Gridd-Search Optimization.\n\nModels are compared as by the results in Aggregate and, later, separated by University. Model performance seems to be better for UTalca than for UAI.\n\nAuthors also perform analysis of Feature Importance and realize that Mat is the most important variable",
          "Homogenous set of students (Engineering despite the 2 Universities).\n\nNo comparison against university specific models.\n\nNoo use of behavioral data (e.g. logs) which could be helpful in obtaining better predictions.\n\nUninspiring Model Performance."
        ]
      ],
      "index": 5
    }
